cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper is about using deep learning for image segmentation, specifically for skin lesion segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of fully convolutional neural networks (FCNNs), which are a type of deep learning model, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper mentions end-to-end learning, which is a common technique in deep learning, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. The paper also uses a public benchmark database, which suggests that it may fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
